### PART 1: GITHUB MCP SERVER IMPLEMENTATION (3-4 HOURS)\
\
__Task 1.1: Set Up GitHub MCP Server__\
\
1. Create a new directory in the Atlas IT repository called `mcp-servers/github-mcp`\
\
2. Initialize a new Node.js project with `npm init -y`\
\
3. Install required dependencies:\
\
   ```bash\
   npm install @octokit/rest @octokit/webhooks @modelcontextprotocol/server dotenv express\
   ```\
\
4. Create a server implementation with these core files:\
\
   - `index.js` - Main entry point\
   - `github-tools.js` - Tool implementations\
   - `github-resources.js` - Resource implementations\
   - `.env.example` - Environment variable template\
\
__Task 1.2: Implement Core GitHub Tools__ Implement the following GitHub API tools:\
\
1. `list_repositories` - List all accessible repositories\
2. `create_issue` - Create a new issue in a repository\
3. `list_pull_requests` - List PRs for a repository\
4. `create_pull_request` - Create a new PR\
5. `get_file_contents` - Get the contents of a file\
6. `update_file` - Update a file in a repository\
7. `run_github_action` - Trigger a GitHub Action workflow\
\
__Task 1.3: Add Workflow Automation Tools__ Implement workflow automation tools:\
\
1. `create_release` - Create a new release with auto-generated notes\
2. `analyze_pr` - Analyze a PR for common issues and provide feedback\
3. `synchronize_labels` - Sync labels across repositories\
4. `generate_changelog` - Generate a changelog from commits\
\
__Task 1.4: Configure Authentication__\
\
1. Implement GitHub App authentication\
2. Add 1Password integration for secure credential storage\
3. Create a configuration file for GitHub organization settings\
\
__Task 1.5: Document the MCP Server__\
\
1. Create a comprehensive README.md with setup instructions\
2. Generate API documentation for all tools\
3. Create example scripts for common operations\
\
