### PART 2: iOS/XCODE MCP SERVER IMPLEMENTATION (3-4 HOURS)\
\
__Task 2.1: Set Up iOS MCP Server__\
\
1. Create a new directory in the Atlas IT repository called `mcp-servers/ios-mcp`\
\
2. Initialize a new Node.js project and install dependencies:\
\
   ```bash\
   npm init -y\
   npm install @modelcontextprotocol/server express child_process fs-extra glob\
   ```\
\
3. Create the core server files:\
\
   - `index.js` - Main entry point\
   - `xcode-tools.js` - Xcode-related tools\
   - `ios-resources.js` - iOS resources\
   - `simulator-tools.js` - iOS Simulator tools\
\
__Task 2.2: Implement Xcode Build Tools__\
\
1. Create `build_xcode_project` - Build an Xcode project\
2. Create `run_xcode_tests` - Run tests for an Xcode project\
3. Create `archive_ios_app` - Create an archive for App Store submission\
4. Create `generate_swift_package` - Generate a Swift package\
\
__Task 2.3: Implement iOS Simulator Tools__\
\
1. Create `list_simulators` - List available iOS simulators\
2. Create `start_simulator` - Start an iOS simulator\
3. Create `install_app` - Install an app on a simulator\
4. Create `take_simulator_screenshot` - Take a screenshot of the simulator\
\
__Task 2.4: Implement Swift Package Tools__\
\
1. Create `create_swift_package` - Create a new Swift package\
2. Create `update_dependencies` - Update Swift package dependencies\
3. Create `add_dependency` - Add a dependency to a Swift package\
4. Create `build_swift_package` - Build a Swift package\
\
__Task 2.5: Document the iOS MCP Server__\
\
1. Create detailed README.md with setup instructions\
2. Create examples for common iOS development workflows\
3. Document integration with CI/CD pipelines\
